      "description": "This 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera is a superlative example of the 996.2 chassis, featuring a mid-mounted 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six that exhibits factory-spec compression and leak-down figures. The drivetrain is anchored by a precise 6-speed manual transaxle, with the essential IMS bearing retrofit and rear main seal replacement already completed to ensure mechanical longevity. The suspension retains its original kinematic integrity, offering razor-sharp turn-in with no discernible bushing compliance or damper fatigue. Equipped with four-piston Brembo monoblock calipers and cross-drilled rotors, the braking system provides exceptional thermal management and tactile feedback. This vehicle is in concours-ready condition, presenting a pristine undercarriage and a flawless exterior that satisfies the most discerning enthusiast's requirements for an analog, high-performance driving machine.",
